{
  "stem": "9245.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They cut out their eyes, and they bound them to-- to the tails of horses and they dragged them through the villages to show the villagers of what's going to happen to them if they are going to assist Jews.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "At this point, it was-- it must've been October-- November of 1942-- partisan movements started getting organized.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I don't mean strictly from Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, it started from escapees from the prisoner of wars camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You know, an awful lot of soldiers got into the prisoners of war.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And Hitler with his regime, treated them like animals, even worse than that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So they escaped, and they started organized group of partisans of-- to fight the front lines, to fight the Germans from the backs.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they appointed-- and they did it already from-- with the-- with the consent of the Politburo of the Russian Communist Party.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They sent one of their guys.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "His name was Kovpac.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He was a partisan in World War I.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He was an older guy already, and he dealt with this kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And he organized a group from about 2,000, 3,000 people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And they were-- their activities were in that area where we were.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And as I said, the majority of them were escapees.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But it wasn't enough, so they went into villages and they plain mobilized the Ukrainian youth to tell them that, you know, this is how they're going to fight the Germans.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "At that point, we were in a desperate situation, meaning myself, my father, my sister, my brother, and also my cousin, with a friend.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We did not know what's going to happen in the winter.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The snow will fall.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There will be the-- the steps.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
